From the manufacturer

UniBond Grout Reviver

This Grout Reviver from UniBond gives new life to faded and discoloured joints. It provides an innovative way of grouting in which the old grout is simply covered with a new layer. Thanks to the especially easy application with the handy pen, there's no need for a pro the job can be done quickly and with ease. Additional tools are not required as the practical container allows for a precise application, even on thin grouts.

Simple Application

The Grout Reviver renews faded and discoloured joints with just a few movements of the hand. Preparation is key, as only then the perfect result can be generated. Surfaces should be completely freed from dirt, mould and contaminants such as residue from shampoo or soap.

Before application the pen needs to be shaken and the nip depressed several times until the product flows. Then the Grout Reviver can be applied directly on the old grout joint in a smooth and even manner. Any excess material can simply be removed with a damp cloth. A second coat can be applied if desired.

The grout needs 60 minutes to dry.

Product Benefits at a Glance:

  • Triple protection against mould
  • Dries in 60 minutes
  • Especially suitable for bathrooms, showers and kitchens
  • Ice white colour
  • Handy pen for a precise application

Easy to Apply

Thanks to the innovative pen shape, grout whitening is made simple with easy and precise application on existing grout lines to restore joints. Refreshing your bathroom or kitchen tiles has never been so easy!

Waterproof and Anti-Mould

The durable grout tile whitening pen refreshes discoloured grout joints and offers triple protection mould resistance to repel, kill and prevent mould. It is also waterproof and dries after just 60 minutes, making it ideal for showers.

Restore and Refresh

Designed to restore and refresh old bathroom grout that has become faded and discoloured for example in the shower cubicle or bathtub wall area, your tile grout will be looking as good as new in no time!

About UniBond

The Henkel brand UniBond offers a wide range of DIY and professional products. The brand emphasises quality, user-friendliness and reliability.

Founded in 1876, Henkel holds globally leading market positions in both the consumer and industrial businesses.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings, help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.

1.0 out of 5 stars Grout reviver pen is a complete joke & con.
Reviewed in the United Kingdom on 26 June 2023
Size Name: 1 x 7mlVerified Purchase
This so called product, (The Unibond grout reviver pen) is the biggest load of rubbish & waste of money I have ever purchased, I consider myself as quite adept at DIY & enjoy taking on most jobs & after decorating my bathroom I realised that due to the condition of my tiles & grout being quite good I would try the aforementioned grout pen to spruce them up, (what a mistake that was to be).
I followed the instructions to the letter which isn't rocket science, shake the pen, press the nib, ( but not too hard ) onto a piece of paper until the liquid is released, ( so far so good ) then gently squeeze ( but not too hard ) onto the grout & gently move along grout line, after doing five 6" tiles the nib split into what looked like frayed string & therefore wouldn't press back into the pen to release the grout liquid rendering it about as useful as a chocolate fire guard.
I spent nearly 12 for 2 of these pathetic, useless, infuriating little pieces of rubbish & ended up actually scraping out & regrouting my tiles which I actually enjoyed doing a lot more than messing about with the aforementioned pile of junk.
This is only my experience & my opinion but please be careful when thinking of buying this product, it's equally annoying as I've bought Unibond products in the past & never had a problem, 0 out of 10 & no stars for this one
